{"lemma":"ذَواقِ","slug":"ذَواقِ","root":"ذ.#.ق","root_slug":"ذ-_-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-_-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14181","n14182"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8E%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ذَاقَ (ḏāqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"taste"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"what is taken of a thing to taste it"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14181","headword_ar":"ذَوَاقٌ","root":"*wq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n.: and also a subst. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is tasted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JM, TA; *) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEaAlN","text_ar":"فَعَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEuwlN","text_ar":"مَفْعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is said of Mohammad,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yakuno ya*um~u *awaAqFA walaA","text_ar":"لَمْ يَكُنْ يَذُمُّ ذَوَاقًا وَلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamodaHuhu","text_ar":"يَمْدَحُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He used not to praise"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what was tasted"},{"kind":"text","text":"[by him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor to dispraise it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (JM.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA *uqotu *awaAqFA","text_ar":"مَا ذُقْتُ ذَوَاقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I tasted not anything."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K. *) ―         -b2-  Hence it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnuwA A_i*aA xarajuwA mino Einodihi laA yatafar~aquwna A_il~aA Eano *awaAqK","text_ar":"كَانُوا اـِذَا خَرَجُوا مِنْ عِنْدِهِ لَا يَتَفَرَّقُونَ اـِلَّا عَنْ ذَوَاقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They used, when they went forth from his"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mohammad's)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"presence, not to disperse themselves save after"},{"kind":"text","text":"receiving]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge and discipline that were, to their minds and souls, as food and drink to their bodies."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JM.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n14182","headword_ar":"ذَوَّاقٌ","root":"*wq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That contracts new marriages time after time:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JM:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick in marrying and quick in divorcing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that conceives frequent disgust"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maluwlN","text_ar":"مَلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S, JM, and Har p. 569),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not remaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in one state with respect to marriage &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har ubi suprà.) Hence the saying, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a A@ll~`ha laA yuHib~u Al*~aw~aAqiyna walaA Al*~aw~aqaAti","text_ar":"اـِنَّ ا@للّٰهَ لَا يُحِبُّ الذَّوَّاقِينَ وَلَا الذَّوَّقَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily God will not love those men who frequently contract new marriages, nor those women who do so"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (JM, and Har ubi suprà.)"}],"source_refs":["JM","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}